A few weeks ago we dined at Gianfranco Restaurant and found the food and service to be excellent.
We so thoroughly enjoyed the experience that we asked a couple , whom are friends and also dine out an average of four nights per week, to join us .
We arrived early, so we decided to begin in the bar area at a hightop table and begin with happy hour prior to ordering from the regular menu.
We ordered appetizers and wine , which was beyond the "happy hour" variety and was enjoying a quiet visit with our friends and noticed the owner happily visiting with the  patrons at the bar, which seemed a nice touch until I saw him gesture toward us and referred to us as "happy hour moochers".
I did not mention this to the others at that time.
Then, as we were beginning to enjoy our meals from the main menu , he (Gianfranco) came close to our table and in a very vial manner, loudly insulted us yet again.
I then asked the waiter what the problem was.
He was very apologetic and asked the G.M.
to come over ,which he did, and he also apologized and offered to buy our dinner.
We were appreciative , however, we rejected his offer.
Gianfranco continued to party with the customers seated at the bar , but , seemed obsessed for some unknown reason by not wanting us there.
We then finished our meals in total discomfort , Paid our bill which totaled $300.00 and quietly departed for the last time ever.
We did notice that only three tables were filled in the main dining room, which based on our bizarre experience may not be just a coincidence.
We have no idea what is wrong with this man.
however , he could be single handedly destroying his own restaurant.
His excellent chefs, waiters and bartender deserve far better than this.
What a tragedy!

